entries.femaleVariant: Bastard! He lobbied them hard for it when they flew in from Tokyo.
Don't look, but that's her. Jenkins' girl.
entries.maleVariant: Don't look, but that's him. Jenkins' boy.

entries.femaleVariant: We're pulling people out of Prague.
Militech hit three of ours.
Now we're evacuating the rest of our facilities in that part of Europe.
What's the status of the three?
I couldn't work with that prick. What do you think they're doin' now?
They need to mop up the leak. The company could lose a boatload.
Director of Special Operations... with his file?
Yeah, because of Frankfurt.
They're dead. Once everyone else is safe, we'll issue a statement to the media.
Saying what?
"A tragic accident during routine security system maintenance" would be my bet.
The Japanese might buy it.
Nuh-uh, they won't. Besides, they're gonna let Night City decide.
Don't wait. Get them out now. Just be discreet.
[Use]
I need your stamp on something. It's possible one of our assets was exposed.
Pull him out.
Keep him digging.
Pull him out. But calmly, don't raise any eyebrows. Otherwise they'll catch on.
Keep him there digging. We invested way too much getting him that deep to back out now.
entries.maleVariant: Keep him there digging. We invested way too much gettin' him that deep to back out now.

entries.femaleVariant: Jenkins will be livid.
You sure...?
Counterintel's doing its damndest to minimize losses.
Three dead. Already this is not minimal.
They'll make sure that stops at three.
Besides, the bigger issue is taking control of the vote.
Is it Frankfurt again?
This is about Frankfurt?
I don't have time for this.
I don't have time for this. I'll handle it later.
No, different issue, local.
I understand... We'll discuss it whenever you have a spare a minute.
Tell me, quick version.
Our agent at Biotechnica suspects they might be onto him.
They recently granted him red security clearance – that's top. He's been fishin' for dirt, but it's been slow.
Your point?
They're clean. Like, we-run-orphanages clean, bleached-server clean. We suspect they flagged him and are feeding him phony data.
Should we greenlight exfil or let him keep looking?
What're the risks?
Projected risks?
Limited threat to life. Not Biotechnica's style. Blackmail's possible, leveraged against false accusations in the media.
The guy has kids, he'd crack.
I'll handle Jenkins.
Understood.
Do I really need to repeat myself?
Oh, of course not.
I have those reports you asked for...
Send them to me. I'm busy.
You're late.
I don't have the time, just send 'em my way.
They were supposed to be ready yesterday.
I'll forward them to your inbox. Uh, apologies for the delay.
Mr. Jenkins asked for you. He's in his office.
I-I know... But I-I have them now.
Send them to my inbox. And you and I will have a word about this later.
Stiffs are one thing, but we can't afford to lose that license.
We've formed a crisis committee and called a meeting.
What is our strategy?
They suspect it's us, but they don't know for certain.
First Frankfurt, now this vote…
I have nothing to add.
No, I didn't say anything of the sort.
That's right, no comment. How many times do I have to say it?
Tell your people to be careful.
They'll be searching for dirt on us now.
Lunar bases are huge to them. They won't forgive us for this.
Did you see the report on the vote? I mean, shit.
The world's going to tear us apart when word gets around.
The world's never going to find out.
And the few who do know the truth... they won't know it for long.
We'll drop a few false leads. Counterintel is already on it.
Ugh, we're in for a damn long day.
[Sit]
[Open drawer]
[Stand]
[Use cognitive booster]
[Close drawer]
[Pick up card]
[Use]
